Package: skmle
Title: Sieve Kernel Maximum Likelihood Estimation for Survival Models
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Dayu Sun [aut, cre] (<dayusun@iu.edu>)
Maintainer: Dayu Sun <dayusun@iu.edu>
Description: Implements estimation and inference for transformed hazards models
    with sparse longitudinal covariates. The package combines
    kernel-weighted log-likelihood and sieve maximum likelihood
    estimation for semiparametric survival analysis when time-dependent
    covariates are observed intermittently. It also provides specialized
    kernel estimating-equation estimators for the proportional hazards
    and additive hazards models, together with simulation and
    cross-validation utilities.
URL: https://dayusun.github.io/skmle/, https://github.com/dayusun/skmle
